  "texts": [
    "To determine the threshold of the minimum correlation coefficient for recognizing the lower activity level stellar sources with consistent Hα profiles in the line center, we analyze the distribution of the minimum correlation coefficient values for the stellar source sample with lower activity levels after the screening conditions described in Sections 3.2.1 and 3.2.2.",
    "The histograms of the distribution are shown in Figure 18c and Figure 18d, which use linear and logarithmic scales on their vertical axes, respectively.",
    "By carefully examining the distribution of the minimum correlation coefficient values and the associated spectral profiles, the lower threshold of the minimum correlation coefficient for recognizing the consistent Hα profiles in the line center for the stellar sources with lower activity levels is determined to be 0.986 (indicated with a horizontal dashed line in Figure 18b and a vertical dashed line in Figure 18c and 18d).",
    "The Hα spectra of a lower activity level stellar source with the minimum correlation coefficient less than the threshold (such as the example shown in Figures 18a and 18b) are regarded to be inconsistent in the line center.",
